AI Flashcards API Documentation

http://127.0.0.1:8000


Generate Flashcards 

URL: /flashcards
Method: Post
Description: Create a group of flashcards.
Request Parameters
No parameters needed
Request Body Object Structure:

[
  {
    "text": string,
    "difficulty": string,
    "card_amount":  integer
  {
[

Request Body Example:

[
  { 
    "difficulty": Easy
    "question": "What is 7+3?",
    "amount": "1"
  }
]

Response Object Structure:

[
  {
    "text": string,
    "difficulty": string,
    "card_amount":  integer,
    "id": integer
  {
[

Reponse Example:

[
  { 
    "id": 1,
    "question": "What is 7+3?",
    "answer": "10"
  },
  {
     "id": 2,
    "question": "What is Georgia's Capitol",
    "answer": "Atlanta"
  },
  {
     "id": 3,
    "question": "Whats the largest Ocean?",
    "answer": "Pacific Ocean"
  },
  {
     "id": 4,
    "question": "What is the shortened name for the element Iridium ",
    "answer": "IR"
  },
  {
     "id": 5,
    "question": "Who created the company Microsoft",
    "answer": "Bill Gates"
  }
]

HTTP Status Codes:
● 201 Created: Successfully created the new flashcard.
● 400 Bad Request: Invalid or incomplete data provided.
● 500 Internal Server Error: Error while fetching flashcard.




Get Flashcards 

URL: /flashcards/{ID}
Method: Get
Description: Gets a single flashcard from list
Request Parameters
No parameters needed
Request Body Object Structure:
No request object needed.
Response Object Structure:

[
  {
    "text": string,
    "difficulty": string,
    "card_amount":  integer
  {
[

Reponse Example:

[
  { 
    "id": 1,
    "question": "What is 7+3?",
    "answer": "10"
  }
]

HTTP Status Codes:
● 200 OK: Successfully retrieved the list of flashcards.
● 500 Internal Server Error: Error while fetching flashcards.



Update Flashcard by ID

URL: /flashcards{ID}
Method: Patch
Description: updates a single flashcard.
Request Parameters
ID: the unique id for the flashcard to be retrieved 
Request Body Object Structure:

[
  {
    "text": string,
    "difficulty": string,
    "card_amount":  integer
  {
[

Response Object Structure:

[
  {
    "text": string,
    "difficulty": string,
    "card_amount":  integer,
    "id": integer
  {
[

Reponse Example:

[
  { 
    "id": 1,
    "question": "What is 7+3?",
    "answer": "10"
  }
]

HTTP Status Codes:
● 201 Created: Successfully created the new flashcard.
● 400 Bad Request: Invalid or incomplete data provided.
● 500 Internal Server Error: Error while fetching flashcard.



Delete Flashcard by ID

URL: /flashcards{ID}
Method: Delete
Description: Deletes a single flashcard.
Request Parameters
ID: the unique id for the flashcard to be retrieved 
Request Body Object Structure:
No request object needed.
Response Object Structure:

[
  {
    "text": string,
    "difficulty": string,
    "card_amount":  integer
  {
[

Response Object Structure

[
  {
    "text": string,
    "difficulty": string,
    "card_amount":  integer,
    "id": integer
  {
[

HTTP Status Codes:
● 201 Created: Successfully created the new flashcard.
● 400 Bad Request: Invalid or incomplete data provided.
● 500 Internal Server Error: Error while fetching flashcard.



Get List of all Flashcards 

URL: /flashcards
Method: Post
Description: Create a list of all flashcards.
Request Parameters
No parameters needed
Request Body Object Structure:
No request object needed.
Response Object Structure:

[
  {
    "text": string,
    "difficulty": string,
    "card_amount":  integer,
    "id": integer
  {
[


Reponse Example:

[
  { 
    "id": 1,
    "question": "What is 7+3?",
    "answer": "10"
  },
  {
     "id": 2,
    "question": "What is Georgia's Capitol",
    "answer": "Atlanta"
  },
  {
     "id": 3,
    "question": "Whats the largest Ocean?",
    "answer": "Pacific Ocean"
  },
  {
     "id": 4,
    "question": "What is the shortened name for the element Iridium ",
    "answer": "IR"
  },
  {
     "id": 5,
    "question": "Who created the company Microsoft",
    "answer": "Bill Gates"
  },
]

HTTP Status Codes:
● 201 Created: Successfully created the new flashcard.
● 400 Bad Request: Invalid or incomplete data provided.
● 500 Internal Server Error: Error while fetching flashcard.
